 London Paralympics when it hosts the fifth round of the Revolution Series next Friday and Saturday. The British Olympic medallists Laura Trott, Jason Kenny and Ed Clancy will be among those back on track. Highlights will be shown on BT Sport, with Joanna Rowsell in the co-commentator's chair.</p><p></p><p>The Lee Valley VeloPark opens for public use on Saturday 31 March. Cyclists can use the iconic track of the velodrome, the BMX&nbsp;course, the floodlit road circuit or mountain biking trails:</p><p><strong>Velodrome track </strong>The 250m track made of finest Siberian pine was where Chris Hoy, Trott, Sarah Storey and the gang led the British gold rush – 12 gold medals across the two Games – 18 months ago. Soon you will be able to go inside The Pringle for&nbsp;a track taster session (£30 adults, £22 concessions). You have to be aged at&nbsp;least&nbsp;12.</p><p><strong>BMX track</strong> Shanaze Reade came sixth here in the Olympic final. Since then the track has been modified to be entirely \"rollable\" – no BMX newcomer need leave the ground before being ready. Minimum age 11. Taster sessions: £15 adults, concession £12.</p><p><strong>Road track </strong>New floodlit, 6m-wide track stretching a mile in length. Minimum age 11. Taster sessions: £15 adults, £12 concession.</p><p><strong>Mountain biking</strong> Five miles of new trails setting off from the Lee Valley VeloPark. Minimum age 11. Taster sessions: £15 adults, £12 concession.</p><p><strong>Full details at</strong>  <a href=\"http://www.visitleevalley.org.uk/en/content/cms/london2012/velo-park/\" title=\"\">visitleevalley.org.uk</a></p>","headline":"London's Olympic Velodrome set to host Revolution and open to the public","trailText":"The Pringle is to open for the first time since the 2012 Paralympic Games this week when it hosts the fifth round of the track cycling competition","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2014/3/8/1394320234296/The-London-Olympic-Velodr-006.jpg"